You are debugging a production issue where a plugin-based Spring application experiences gradual Metaspace growth and eventually crashes with `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace` after hot-reloading dynamic modules. The reloading logic is managed by this component:

java
@Component
public class PluginManager {
    private final Map<String, CustomClassLoader> activeLoaders = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public void reloadPlugin(String path, String pluginId) throws Exception {
        CustomClassLoader oldLoader = activeLoaders.remove(pluginId);
        if (oldLoader != null) {
            oldLoader.close(); 
        }

        CustomClassLoader newLoader = new CustomClassLoader(new URL[]{new File(path).toURI().toURL()}, this.getClass().getClassLoader());
        Class<?> pluginClass = newLoader.loadClass("com.example.DynamicPlugin");
        Object pluginInstance = pluginClass.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();

        // Register dynamic bean definitions in the Spring context
        activeLoaders.put(pluginId, newLoader);
    }
}

